trend_summary: Built-up area expands each epoch, with new subdivisions filling north-west, north-central and eastern sectors. Highways and feeder roads lengthen, enabling light-industrial estates and commerce clusters. Forest and farmland patches shrink, although some interior greenspace persists. Overall character shifts from semi-rural toward a continuous, medium-density suburban fabric.
notable_changes: Large residential subdivisions infill the north-west quadrant, replacing woodland.
New highway interchange and widened arterial roads appear in the centre, improving connectivity.
Light-industrial/commercial zone with large white roofs emerges in the north-east.
Progressive clearing of forest along the eastern boundary for development.
Farmland in the south-west transitions to mixed residential and commercial use.
